Comment: So I do the same as before.
And he plays the Budapest again.
I continue following our earlier game.
I continue with the note from my annotation.

This seems best for black. Now I was originally going to continue with 5. f2-f4, but I realised that in that position Qd8-h4 check is very strong for him. However I though so what? I can develop a little and then play it at a later stage.
He throws in a Bishop check.
I block in such a way that he can't destroy my pawn formation with by taking my knight, which he could have done if I'd played Nc3.
I think this is wrong. I think the trust h7-h5 more or less means black has to castle on the queen side. As such he should be developing his queen side pieces and preparing to castle queen side.
